	<div class="row">
		<div class="column">
			<div class="caption">
				Studies vary and these numbers are estimates. Women tend to be at the higher end of the ranges given. Preliminary studies of African Americans suggest that their risk may be somewhat higher.
			</div>
			<h2>The Gene Test Does Not Offer 100% Certainty</h2>
			<p>If the e4 gene is present, a person&rsquo;s risk goes up - but never to 100%.</p>
			<div class="panel">
				<div class="panel-header">
					It&rsquo;s important to keep in mind that:
				</div>
				<div class="panel-body">
					<ul>
						<li>
							Many people who have the e4 gene will not develop Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.
						</li>
						<li>Many people who do not have the e4 gene will develop Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.</li>
						<li>Researchers believe there may be additional genes associated with Alzheimer&rsquo;s that have not been identified yet.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			<p><span class="red">Note:</span> The cost for the APOE gene test currently ranges from $100 to about $400, depending on the laboratory. For greatest accuracy, genetic testing should be done by a 
				<%= link_to "CLIA-certified laboratory", glossary_path(anchor: "clia-certified"), target: "blank" %>.</p>
			<p class="further-resources-link">
				To learn more about APOE Gene Tests <%= link_to "see Resources.", further_resources_path(anchor: "understanding"), target: "blank" %>
			</p>
